\": 0.609067677980149, \"rank\": 0.6418426765701595, \"text\": \"Omar\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Umar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Umar\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Historically, Egypt has secured four Olympic medals in boxing.\", \"from\": 575, \"to\": 637, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 589, \"end\": 594, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt\", \"score\": 0.9829497996949982, \"rank\": 0.01734593163864122, \"text\": \"Egypt\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The first was a bronze medal won by AbdelMoneim El-Gendy in Rome 1960.\", \"from\": 638, \"to\": 708, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 698, \"end\": 707, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1960_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999543613295, \"rank\": 4.563513227093995e-08, \"text\": \"Rome 1960\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1960_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1960_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Subsequently, Mohamed El-Sayed and Ahmed Ismail each earned bronze medals, while Mohamed Ali clinched a silver medal at the Athens 2004 Olympics in Greece.\", \"from\": 709, \"to\": 864, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 723, \"end\": 739, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mohamed_El-Sayed_(Qatari_footballer)\", \"score\": 0.7894672324521592, \"rank\": 0.266666666666641, \"text\": \"Mohamed El-Sayed\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mohamed_El-Sayed_(Qatari_footballer)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mohamed_El-Sayed_(Qatari_footballer)\"}, {\"begin\": 750, \"end\": 756, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isma'il_Pasha\", \"score\": 0.9999999548135757, \"rank\": 4.4908668551001995e-08, \"text\": \"Ismail\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q21